hints.content: When we skip count by hundreds,  we add $100$ to each number as we count.

Kaley started with $561$,  so we need to add $100$ more to $561$.

$561 + 100 = 661$

The next number Kaley will say is $561$.

Kaley is still skip counting by hundreds so we need to add $100$ to $661$.

$661+ 100 = 761$

The next number Kaley will say is $761$.
